  issn = {0067-0049},
  doi = {10.1086/320854},
  abstract = {CHIANTI provides a database of atomic energy levels, wavelengths, 
radiative transition probabilities, and electron excitation data for a
large number of ions of astrophysical interest. It also includes a suite
of Interactive Data Language programs to calculate optically thin
synthetic spectra and to perform spectral analysis and plasma
diagnostics. This database allows the calculation of theoretical line
emissivities necessary for the analysis of optically thin emission-line
spectra. The first version (1.01) of the CHIANTI database was released
in 1996 and published by Dere et al. in 1997 as Paper I in this series.
The second version, released in 1999 by Landi et al., included continuum
emission and data for additional ions. Both versions of the CHIANTI
database have been used extensively by the astrophysical and solar
communities to analyze emission-line spectra from astrophysical sources.
Now the CHIANTI database has been extended to wavelengths shorter than
50 {\AA} by including atomic data for the hydrogen and helium
isoelectronic sequences, inner-shell transitions and satellite lines,
and several other ions. In addition, some of the ions already present in
the database have been updated and extended with new atomic data from
published calculations.},
